### ============================================================
### 1. REGISTRO DE USUARIO — POST /api/user/register
### Esperado: 201 con accessToken, refreshToken y { email, status, role }
### ============================================================

POST {{baseUrl}}/user/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "pablo@bildyapp.com",
  "password": "pass909090"
}

###

### Email inválido → 400 (validación Zod)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "no-es-un-email",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### Contraseña menor de 8 caracteres → 400 (validación Zod)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "bob@bildyapp.com",
  "password": "123"
}

###

### Email ya verificado → 409 Conflict
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@bildyapp.com",
  "password": "password123"
}


### ============================================================
### 2. VALIDACIÓN DEL EMAIL — PUT /api/user/validation
### Requiere: accessToken del registro
### Código: consultarlo en MongoDB Atlas → campo verificationCode
### Esperado: 200 con mensaje de confirmación
### ============================================================

PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/validation HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "code": "425111"
}

###

### Código incorrecto → 400 con intentos restantes
PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/validation HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "code": "000000"
}

###

### Código con menos de 6 dígitos → 400 (validación Zod)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/validation HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "code": "123"
}

###

### Sin token → 401 Unauthorized
PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/validation HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "code": "123456"
}


### ============================================================
### 3. LOGIN — POST /api/user/login
### Esperado: 200 con accessToken, refreshToken y datos del usuario
### ============================================================

POST {{baseUrl}}/user/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "pablo@bildyapp.com",
  "password": "pass909090"
}

###

### Contraseña incorrecta → 401 Unauthorized
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alice@bildyapp.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### Email no registrado → 401 Unauthorized
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/login HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "noexiste@bildyapp.com",
  "password": "password123"
}


### ============================================================
### 4a. ONBOARDING: DATOS PERSONALES — PUT /api/user/register
### Requiere: accessToken
### Esperado: 200 con usuario actualizado
### ============================================================

PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "name": "Pablo",
  "lastName": "García",
  "nif": "99945678B"
}

###

### Sin nombre → 400 (validación Zod)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "lastName": "García",
  "nif": "12345678A"
}

###

### Sin token → 401 Unauthorized
PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/register HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Alice",
  "lastName": "García",
  "nif": "12345678A"
}


### ============================================================
### 4b. ONBOARDING: DATOS DE COMPAÑÍA — PATCH /api/user/company
### Requiere: accessToken
### CIF no existe → crea Company nueva, role se mantiene admin
### CIF ya existe → se une a la Company, role cambia a guest
### ============================================================

### Crear compañía nueva (CIF no existe en BD)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/user/company HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "name": "Nike",
  "cif": "B12345633",
  "address": {
    "street": "Calle España",
    "number": "89",
    "postal": "26789",
    "city": "Madrid",
    "province": "Madrid"
  },
  "isFreelance": false
}

###

### Unirse a compañía existente (mismo CIF → role pasa a guest)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/user/company HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "name": "Renault F1 Team",
  "cif": "B12345679",
  "isFreelance": false
}

###

### Autónomo (isFreelance: true → usa datos personales del usuario)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/user/company HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "cif": "12345678A",
  "isFreelance": true
}

###

### Sin CIF → 400 (validación Zod)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/user/company HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "name": "Obras García S.L.",
  "isFreelance": false
}


### ============================================================
### 5. LOGO DE LA COMPAÑÍA — PATCH /api/user/logo
### Requiere: accessToken + tener company asignada
### Usar Postman/Thunder Client para subir el archivo
### Body: form-data → key "logo" (tipo File) → selecciona imagen
### Esperado: 200 con la Company actualizada con campo logo
### ============================================================

### Con REST Client no se puede subir archivos bien.
### Usa Postman con:
Method: PATCH
URL: http://localhost:3000/api/user/logo
Header: Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJfaWQiOiI2OWQ0MmFjZjdiNmYyNThlMmI5YTUwYzIiLCJyb2xlIjoiYWRtaW4iLCJpYXQiOjE3NzU1MTI0NzksImV4cCI6MTc3NTUxOTY3OX0.O4qq6zXeNkNuU7pZBXEE6IRk3ILqUCTWlkCY4V_JDFc
Body: form-data → key=logo, type=File, value=imagen.png


### ============================================================
### 6. OBTENER USUARIO — GET /api/user
### Requiere: accessToken
### Esperado: 200 con usuario completo + Company populada + fullName
### ============================================================

GET {{baseUrl}}/user/me HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Sin token → 401 Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/user HTTP/1.1

###

### Token inválido → 401 Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/user HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer token_invalido_123


### ============================================================
### 7a. REFRESH TOKEN — POST /api/user/refresh
### Esperado: 200 con nuevo accessToken y refreshToken
### ============================================================

POST {{baseUrl}}/user/refresh HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "cb076eb01b735fb33d8df35e4adae270bd3f7073525cff397e0331a3707de71bce75eea5882c4b882f02ff595749c71067fd401533293d5a8aa3571ad9e5a63c"
}

###

### Token inválido → 401 Unauthorized
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/refresh HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "token_invalido_o_ya_usado"
}

###

### Sin refreshToken → 400 (validación Zod)
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/refresh HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{}


### ============================================================
### 7b. LOGOUT — POST /api/user/logout
### Requiere: accessToken
### Esperado: 200 con mensaje de confirmación
### Después del logout el refreshToken queda invalidado
### ============================================================

POST {{baseUrl}}/user/logout HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Intentar refresh después del logout → 401
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/refresh HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}


### ============================================================
### 8. ELIMINAR USUARIO — DELETE /api/user
### Requiere: accessToken
### ?soft=true → borrado lógico (deleted: true en BD)
### sin parámetro → borrado físico (desaparece de MongoDB)
### Esperado: 204 No Content
### ============================================================

### Soft delete → el usuario queda con deleted: true
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/user/delete?soft=true HTTP/1.1
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Hard delete → el documento desaparece de MongoDB
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/user/delete
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

###

### Sin token → 401 Unauthorized
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/user HTTP/1.1


### ============================================================
### 9. CAMBIAR CONTRASEÑA — PUT /api/user/password (BONUS)
### Requiere: accessToken
### Esperado: 200 con mensaje de confirmación
### ============================================================

PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/password HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "currentPassword": "password777",
  "newPassword": "newPassword456"
}

###

### Nueva igual a la actual → 400 (refine de Zod)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/password HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "currentPassword": "password777",
  "newPassword": "password777"
}

###

### Contraseña actual incorrecta → 400
PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/password HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "currentPassword": "wrongpassword",
  "newPassword": "newPassword456"
}

###

### Nueva contraseña menor de 8 chars → 400 (validación Zod)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/user/password HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "currentPassword": "password123",
  "newPassword": "123"
}


### ============================================================
### 10. INVITAR COMPAÑERO — POST /api/user/invite
### Requiere: accessToken de usuario con role ADMIN
### Esperado: 201 con datos del nuevo usuario creado
### ============================================================

### Admin invita → 201
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/invite HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "email": "bob@bildyapp.com",
  "name": "Bob",
  "lastName": "Martínez"
}

###

### Email ya registrado → 409 Conflict
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/invite HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

{
  "email": "alice@bildyapp.com",
  "name": "Alice",
  "lastName": "García"
}

###

### Token de guest intenta invitar → 403 Forbidden
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/invite HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN_DE_USUARIO_GUEST

{
  "email": "carol@bildyapp.com",
  "name": "Carol",
  "lastName": "López"
}

###

### Sin token → 401 Unauthorized
POST {{baseUrl}}/user/invite HTTP/1.1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "dave@bildyapp.com"
}


